05/08/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) on Wednesday (4 August) outlined the rules under which candidates hoping to run in the autumn general elections will be selected. 
According to the guidelines, prospective PSD candidates must get 1,000 signatures of support and must declare their assets and other interests. 
The PSD wants 30 per cent of its candidates to be young people and 25 per cent to be women. 
(Mediafax - 04/08/04)
